## 1. DMS Single Source of Truth Rule (Non-Negotiable)

After DMS.6 is complete:

```
✅ ALL document files must be stored in DMS (dms_documents + dms_document_files)

✅ ALLOWED — stay in ERP module tables:
  party_licenses         (structured: license number, expiry, authority — NOT a file)
  party_tax_registrations (structured: TRN number, effective dates — NOT a file)
  party_compliance_profiles (structured: approval status, risk — NO files)

❌ PROHIBITED after DMS.6:
  Creating employee_documents table
  Creating vehicle_documents table
  Creating equipment_documents table
  Creating project_documents table
  Any new *_documents table for any ERP module
  Writing to party_documents.file_path (column is deprecated placeholder)
```

For all future ERP modules that need document attachments:
```typescript
// CORRECT — use generic link
await createDmsDocumentLink({
  documentId: dmsDocId,
  entityType: 'vehicle',  // or 'employee', 'project', etc.
  entityId: vehicleId,
});

// WRONG — do not create module-specific tables
// ALTER TABLE vehicles ADD COLUMN document_id BIGINT; ← NEVER
// CREATE TABLE vehicle_documents (...); ← NEVER
```

