## 5. `party_documents` Migration Status

**Current status (pre-DMS.6):** `party_documents` is an ACTIVE but metadata-only table. The `file_path`, `file_name`, `file_mime_type`, `file_size` columns have ALWAYS been NULL — no files were ever stored.

**During DMS.6:**
- Metadata rows migrate to `dms_documents` + `dms_document_links(entity_type='party')`
- `party_licenses.license_document_id` FK altered to point to `dms_documents`
- `party_tax_registrations.certificate_document_id` FK altered to point to `dms_documents`
- `party_documents` marked deprecated (30-day soak period)
- `MASTER_PARTY_DOCUMENT` numbering rule disabled

**After DMS.6:**
- `party_documents` is read-only (no inserts, no updates)
- `party_document_types` is read-only (new types go to `dms_document_types`)
- `getPartyDocumentTypes()` server action replaced by `getDmsDocumentTypes()`

